<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12207h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12207h">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12207h"> 207(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> derri&egrave;re le fromager</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Un jour, il arriva que le p&egrave;re, &eacute;tant fatigu&eacute;, dit &agrave; son fils: &ldquo;S&eacute;ri, pioche <font color="green">[la terre]</font> jusqu&apos;&agrave; ce que je revienne; je vais m&apos;absenter <font color="green">[litt&eacute;ralement &ldquo;je vais aller <mark>derri&egrave;re le fromager</mark>&rdquo;, expression polie pour dire qu&apos;on va satisfaire ses besoins]</font>. <br><font color="green">[One day it happened that a tired father said to his son: &ldquo;Seri, plough the earth until I come back, I will go away now&rdquo; (literally, &ldquo;I will go behind the kapok&rdquo;, a polite expression for to satisfy one&apos;s needs.]</font> <small> Maurice Delafosse, <a name="LNEG" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#LNEG"><cite title="source">L'&acirc;me n&egrave;gre</cite></a> (1922) 162 (from Chapter XXI, <i>Plaisanterie</i>, the story <i>A menteur, menteur et demi</i>)</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
